About
Wentworth Golf Club
Wentworth Golf Club
18 Holes
Driving Range
Par 71
6,459 yards
Slope 144
Rating 71.5
Bermuda Grass
Our exquisite championship golf course, designed by Steve Smyers in 1990 (the same architect behind the renowned Tampa gem, Old Memorial), gracefully winds through natural, undulating terrain teeming with wildlife. The front nine offers a secluded escape, surrounded by moss-covered oaks and gently rolling fairways, devoid of any residential distractions.
Transitioning to the back nine, water hazards come into play, challenging golfers with demanding tee shots that demand both distance and precision. Prepare to bring your best game, as each hole has been meticulously crafted to test players of all skill levels. Despite its modest length of 6,500 yards from the tips, the narrow fairways create an illusion of greater length.
The Wentworth golf experience is enhanced by the elegant English Manor Clubhouse, evoking the ambiance of an upscale private facility. It‚Äôs worth noting that Wentworth is open to the public and warmly welcomes golfers of all levels.
Book Online
The Course Tour
As someone said, ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs one of the longest short courses you‚Äôll ever play.‚Äù Once you play the course you‚Äôll know what they were talking about.
The front nine winds through a typical Florida woodlands with nary a home to be seen. You‚Äôll find Number 2 especially challenging, but the rest of the front side will test all aspects of your game, with both short and long par 3‚Äôs and par 4‚Äôs. And there‚Äôs plenty of water and sand to keep you honest and staying in the short grass.
The back side is just as challenging with one of the most challenging par 3‚Äôs you‚Äôll find anywhere in Hole 14. Again a mixture of short and long, and easy and difficult make your round interesting.
And don‚Äôt think that once you get on the green the hard work is over. Every green is undulating and challenging. The greens average between 10 and 11 on the stimpmeter, so you better be able to roll your rock if you want to make your par.
Practice Facilities
Experience golf improvement at its finest at Wentworth Golf Club‚Äôs exceptional practice facility in Tarpon Springs. Our meticulously designed practice area offers an array of amenities tailored to elevate your game.
Take your swings to new heights on our expansive driving range, where you can fine-tune your long shots, working on distance and accuracy. Aspiring putters can perfect their touch on our spacious practice putting green, while those looking to master the art of the short game will find our dedicated short game area, complete with a challenging sand bunker, indispensable for honing their skills.
Whether you‚Äôre a seasoned pro or just starting your golf journey, our practice facility welcomes golfers of all levels to enhance their abilities and gain the confidence they need to conquer the course.

The Pro Shop
We've got what you need to hit the course!
Stop by and grab the latest in golf gear or just pick up some golf balls and tees before your next round of golf! Our pro shop is always freshly stocked with what you need to hit the course running!
